<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="73" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                    <head>No. 379.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-01-30"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 30,
                            1873</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>In view of the frequent interruption of communications by telegraph and post
                        between Madrid and the frontier, and having reasons to anticipate very soon
                        a change in the form of this government, I beg you to instruct me as to my
                        line of conduct in case the existing Congress shall declare itself a
                        convention and appoint a new executive.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed><persName corresp="#p_DES1">SICKLES</persName>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>